    • Uses of Validator in de.mdelab.simulator.mrubis.validators

      Classes in de.mdelab.simulator.mrubis.validators that implement Validator 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  MRubisAvgResponseTimeValidator
      Validates for each Tenant architecture the average response time for the personalized item search, that is, for the method MRubisNames.getPersonalizedItems_Signature of the interface MRubisNames.browseCategoriesService_InterfaceType_FqName based on the corresponding PerformanceStats elements.
      class  MRubisFilterOrderAnalyzer
      Validates for each Tenant architecture the ordering of filter Components in the pipe.
      class  MRubisFilterTypeValidator
      Validates that each filter Component of a Tenant's pipe is of a different filter ComponentType.
      class  MRubisMinConfigurationValidator
      Validates for the minimal configuration of each Tenant architecture in terms of provided interfaces and the number of components providing each interface within one tenant.
      class  MRubisMissingMonitoredPropertyValidator
      Validates the model after a self-adaptation to check whether all filter Components have a MonitoredProperty for the selection rate and a MonitoredProperty for the local computation time.
      class  MRubisPipeAdaptationValidator
      Validates a self-adaptation of a pipe of filter Components and reacts to the self-adaptation by changing the performance stats in the model as if the self-adaptation impacts the performance of the managed system.
      class  MRubisPipeCycleValidator
      Validates the pipe of filter Components in each Tenant architecture whether the pipe contains any cycle among the filter components or not.
      class  MRubisPipeSizeValidator
      Validates the pipe of filter Components in each Tenant architecture whether the pipe contains at least so many filter components as the given threshold.
      class  MRubisRequiredInterfaceValidator
      Validates for each Tenant architecture whether each RequiredInterface is connected to a ProvidedInterface of a ComponentState.STARTED Component within the same Tenant and whether the connected RequiredInterface and ProvidedInterface are of the same InterfaceType.

    • Uses of Validator in de.mdelab.simulator.validators

      Classes in de.mdelab.simulator.validators that implement Validator 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ComponentLifeCycleAdaptationValidator
      Validates a self-adaptation that adjust the life cycle state of a Component (see Component.getState()), for instance, to start or stop a component.
      class  ComponentReplacementValidator
      Validates a self-adaptation whether it replaces a Component with a Component of another ComponentType.
      class  ComponentStateValidator
      Retrieves all Components of all Tenant architectures ordered by their states (see Component.getState() and grouped by their Tenants.
      class  ExceptionValidator
      Validates for each Tenant architecture if and how many Exceptions are thrown by ProvidedInterfaces.
      class  MinConfigurationValidator
      Validates for a minimal configuration of each Tenant architecture.
      class  ParameterValidator
      Validates for each Tenant architecture whether each Parameter of a ComponentState.STARTED Component has a value assigned (see Parameter.getValue()).
      class  ProvidedInterfaceValidator
      Validates each Tenant architecture whether its ComponentState.STARTED Components provide together all given interfaces such that the tenant actually provides the necessary functionality to be operable.
      class  RequiredInterfaceValidator
      Validates for each Tenant architecture whether each RequiredInterface is connected to a ProvidedInterface of a ComponentState.STARTED Component within the same Tenant.
